EADS North America CEO in Alaska plane crash
NEW YORK (MarketWatch) -- The European Aeronautic Defence & Space Co. fr:ead EADSY, -0.18% confirmed Tuesday its head of North American operations was a passenger on a private aircraft that crashed in Alaska, leaving five people dead. It was not immediately known if EADS North America Chief Executive Sean O'Keefe was among the fatalities, a company spokesperson said. O'Keefe and former Sen. Ted Stevens (R, Alaska) were reportedly en route to a fishing lodge with seven other people when the plane crashed Monday night in wilderness near Aleknagik, Alaska. Five of the nine people on board were killed, the National Transportation Safety Board said. No other details were immediately available.